    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-04-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-04-18T18:00:00-05:00" n="20"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d20">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856.48/4–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-04-18T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 18, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1556. For Reber. The Department on April 4 approved a British-Netherlands plan
                    for immediate shipment of relief foodstuffs up to 5,000 tons weekly to occupied
                    Netherlands by neutral means and under adequate safeguards. The Department is
                    now informed that a proposal approved by the British military and Foreign Office
                    for dropping daily by air a large amount of supplies into German occupied
                    Netherlands may be referred to SHAEF. In such case you may advise SHAEF that the
                    Department would approve the additional introduction of foodstuffs into occupied
                    Holland but only if there appears to be reasonable assurance that such
                    foodstuffs would in fact reach Netherlands hands.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
